{"references": [224839970, 271761304, 223217209, 265372318], "title": "Multivariate Clustering Procedures with Variable Metrics", "abstract": "Several multivariate clustering methods are analyzed in which each cluster may have a different metric depending on its covariance matrix. Numerical experiments show that the only reliable method among these is one using a metric suggested by Rohlf [1970] based on the within cluster covariance matrix normalized for unit determinant. (12 references.)", "authors": ["Ricardo Maronna", "Pablo M. Jacovkis"], "citations": [34080758, 265522289, 220601375, 31002185, 267137913, 224377472, 227596388, 226186082, 239061303, 247074351], "id": 265372318}